<p>
<seg id=1> The Palestinian leader Yaser Arafat began his first official flight departing from Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=2> The airport began operations one day before. </seg>
<seg id=3> On Wednesday Israeli security officials saw him off when Arafat's plane departed for Paris. </seg>
<seg id=4> Israel is responsible for the airport's security. </seg>
<seg id=5> The newly signed land-for-peace agreement by Israel and Palestine cleared the way for the use of the airport. </seg>
<seg id=6> Palestinians take the airport as a symbol of their sovereignty and a great boost to Palestine's economy. </seg>
</p>
